00:13:32,597 --> 00:13:39,099
I had uncredited writing chops and that production creative team experience, but it really wasn't sure how to

261
00:13:39,699 --> 00:13:42,440
Make the transition. There's no clear roadmap

262
00:13:42,980 --> 00:13:48,321
Everybody says a little bit different, you know gives you a little bit different type of advice for how to break in

263
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:52,362
But it's very difficult if you're on the outside to figure out what that track is

264
00:13:53,863 --> 00:13:56,683
What skills that I had which which skills were applicable? I

